    "body": "### Steps to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ spack install py-torch@1.8.1 % gcc@8.3.0\r\n\r\n-- Building version 1.8.1\r\nCould not find <path>/spack-src/third_party/gloo/CMakeLists.txt.\r\nDid you run 'git submodule update --init --recursive\r\n==> Error.\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\nThis issue only occurs on an air-gap system.  I cannot attached build logs.\r\n\r\n### General information\r\n\r\nI'm not sure how the installer is supposed to access these *third_party* sources.  Does spack have a way to provide these as externals?  Is anyone else trying to build `py-torch` on an air gap system?\r\n\r\n",
